JMX over RMI and firewalls do not get along too well (Here is an 
umbrella posting on the issue: 
http://forum.java.sun.com/thread.jspa?threadID=717761&messageID=4148704). 

You might trying having heritrix start up the html adapter on a port you 
can access through your firewall.  The adapter can be found in the 
jmxtools jar in the jmx reference implementation (Download the 1.2.1 
reference implementation off this page: 
http://java.sun.com/javase/technologies/core/mntr-mgmt/javamanagement/download.jsp).  
If you go this route, let us know how it goes for you.

Thanks,
St.Ack



